I can only imagine what an extraordinary contribution so many of that generation of women would have made with a full range of choices but there is ample evidence that they created a generation driven by the values they gave us and you are a true example of this @billshortenmp

She raised a daughter and four sons with a deep respect for education, equality and responsibility to help others. With a group of local ladies she helped set up the first women’s refuge in Warilla in the early 70’s and lives her values every day.

Like so many sharing their stories my Mum had the intellect and ability to have had a career in any field she wanted but had to leave school, worked in a cake shop, married and had five kids then went to work in a MP’s office and was highly respected by all she worked with

#MyMum Thank you @billshortenmp for so powerfully telling the story of an amazing generation of women like my Mum-denied a full education and careers and later facing age & gender discrimination in the workforce
